The old_p / old_basis columns are the values from run_anchor_integrity.R.
They are shown for PROVENANCE ONLY, never as a like-for-like comparison:
  - the old panel was MyDNA-merged, so its SNP set was intersected down
    to a 23andMe v5 chip before any extract ran;
  - the old site extract additionally carried Minoan_OTHER, a population
    its own model never used, which cost ~33,000 SNPs;
  - the old site arm defined sub-pools by Locality substring; this one
    uses AADR's own Group IDs.
